<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="454" pageId="2" pageNumber="453" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1666,2018]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,152,251]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="454" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1882,1909]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(male). 
<emphasis box="[413,530,1883,1910]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">Antenna 1</emphasis>
peduncular articles 2 and 3 short, each about 2 × as long as broad. 
<emphasis box="[1319,1436,1883,1910]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">Antenna 2</emphasis>
slightly incrassate. 
<emphasis box="[371,520,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">Gnathopod 1</emphasis>
merus posterior margin unexpanded; carpus:propodus length ratio = 1:0.7; dactylus long, more than one third length of propodus. Pereopod 6 basis expanded, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1071,1430,1954,1981]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">posterior margin sub-straight</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,347,1990,2018]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,1990,2018]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">Pereopod 7</emphasis>
basis
</emphasis>
expanded, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[475,1436,1990,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="453">posterior margin flattened; propodus 7 × as long as broad; dactylus elongate and</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,153,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">slender.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[249,346,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Uropods</emphasis>
short. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[422,953,152,179]" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[422,529,152,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Uropod 1</emphasis>
rami shorter than peduncle (1:0.7);
</emphasis>
endopod slightly longer than exopod; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Uro- pod 2</emphasis>
rami subequal with each other and subequal with peduncle
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[942,1049,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="454">Uropod 3</emphasis>
peduncle almost as broad as long; ramus short, broad, not markedly tapering distally, with 4-5 marginal setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
